<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="15" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="16.[824,1528,1253,1577]" pageId="16" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis box="[920,1207,1254,1282]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="15">Diagnostic Features.</emphasis>
This new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Yin, Bao and Zhang, 1995" authorityName="Yin, Bao and Zhang" authorityYear="1995" box="[965,1528,1290,1319]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Lycosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis box="[965,1152,1291,1319]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="15">Lycosa vittata</emphasis>
Yin, 
<bibRefCitation author="BARRION AT &amp; LITSINGER JA" bookContentInfo="700 p." box="[1235,1528,1290,1319]" journalOrPublisher="CABI and IRRI" pageId="16" pageNumber="15" refString="BARRION AT, LITSINGER JA. 1995. Riceland Spiders of South and Southeast Asia. CABI and IRRI, Manila, Philippines, 700 p." title="Riceland Spiders of South and Southeast Asia" type="book" year="1995">
Bao and Zhang, 
<date box="[1464,1528,1290,1319]" pageId="16" pageNumber="15" value="1995">
<number box="[1464,1528,1290,1319]" pageId="16" pageNumber="15" value="1995.0">1995</number>
</date>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
but separated from the latter in the following characters, (
<number box="[981,994,1364,1393]" pageId="16" pageNumber="15" value="1.0">1</number>
) spination and number of trichobothrium in tibia IV, (
<number box="[993,1010,1401,1430]" pageId="16" pageNumber="15" value="2.0">2</number>
) subequal length of tibia I and III, (
<number box="[1501,1517,1401,1430]" pageId="16" pageNumber="15" value="3.0">3</number>
) blunt tip and sigmoid median apophysis, (
<number box="[1389,1407,1437,1466]" pageId="16" pageNumber="15" value="4.0">4</number>
) ratio of width [a] over length [b] of median apophysis = 
<number box="[1463,1523,1474,1503]" pageId="16" pageNumber="15" value="0.4">0.40</number>
, (
<number box="[834,850,1511,1540]" pageId="16" pageNumber="15" value="5.0">5</number>
) 
<number box="[871,903,1511,1540]" pageId="16" pageNumber="15" value="90.0">90</number>
0 position of thin and needle-like embolus, and (
<number box="[834,851,1548,1577]" pageId="16" pageNumber="15" value="6.0">6</number>
) V-shaped yellow apical margin of the labium.
</paragraph>
